The CSS Box Model
The CSS box model represents each HTML element as a box. This box consists of four main parts:

Content: The area that contains the element's actual content (text, images, etc.).
Padding: The space between the content and the border.
Border: The outer edge of the box.
Margin: The space between the border of the box and other elements.
Example HTML and CSS
HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Box Model Example</title>
    <style>
        .box {
            width: 200px;
            height: 100px;
            border: 1px solid black;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: lightblue;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="box">This is a box.</div>
</body>
</html>
Use code with caution.

