Effect of Changing Components
Padding: Increasing padding adds space between the content and the border, making the element larger without affecting its width and height.
Margin: Increasing margin adds space between the border of the element and other elements, creating more space around it.
Border: Increasing the border width adds space to the outer edge of the box, making it larger.
Example: Changing Padding and Margin
HTML
<style>
    .box {
        /* ... other properties ... */
        padding: 40px;
        margin: 40px;
    }
</style>
Use code with caution.

This will double the padding and margin, making the box significantly larger and creating more space around it.

By understanding the CSS box model and its components, you can effectively control the layout and spacing of elements on a web page, creating a visually appealing and well-organized design.